 "context": {
  "patient_ref": "MRN2970753705",
  "text": "# Abnormal Uterine Bleeding Evaluation\n\n## Context\n\nThe current date and time is 2022-02-06T23:17:00+00:00. You are an Obstetrician-Gynecologist at an academic medical center outpatient clinic (Practitioner ID: dr-teresa-hayes). A primary care provider has flagged a patient (MRN2970753705) for gynecology review regarding persistent intermenstrual spotting.\n\n## Your Task\n\n1. **Review the patient's clinical history**\n   - Retrieve demographics and relevant medical history\n   - Review recent lab results including thyroid function and prolactin levels\n   - Examine clinical notes documenting the bleeding pattern and timeline\n   - Note any recent screening tests or procedures performed\n\n2. **Assess the clinical presentation**\n   - Characterize the abnormal bleeding pattern\n   - Identify potential etiologies based on patient age and history\n   - Evaluate completeness of the initial workup\n\n3. **Develop a diagnostic plan**\n   - Determine appropriate imaging studies to evaluate structural causes\n   - Consider additional laboratory testing if clinically indicated\n   - Document rationale for recommended workup\n\n4. **Document clinical recommendations**\n   - Summarize key findings and clinical reasoning\n   - Specify imaging orders with appropriate modalities\n   - Address treatment options for symptom management (e.g., hormonal therapy if appropriate)\n   - Outline contingency plans if initial workup is unrevealing\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- Clinical assessment and management plan saved to `/workspace/output/aub_evaluation_note.txt`\n"
 },
